outputs: Open Research Data (ORD) Program Project Metadata and Report Data

Source: R/outputs.R
outputs.Rd

This data package contains metadata and report data from over 60 research projects funded by the joint Open Research Data (ORD) program of ETH Zurich, EPFL, and the four research institutes of the ETH Domain from 2020-2023. The package includes project-level metadata, such as project titles, descriptions, and categorizations (Establish, Explore, Contribute), as well as data extracted from reports submitted by each project, providing insights into the projects' objectives, methods, outcomes, and impacts.

Usage

outputs

Format

A tibble with 60 rows and 7 variables

project_id

A unique identifier for each project, represented as a numerical value.

item_id

A unique identifier for each item within a project, represented as a numerical value with decimal places.

item_name_long

A detailed name describing the item, such as 'New or enhanced webs' or 'New or enhanced data'.

item_name_short

A brief name summarizing the item, such as 'website', 'repository', or 'dataset'.

quantity

The number of items, represented as a discrete numerical value.

description

A text description providing additional context about the item.

link

A URL linking to the item or its associated webpage.
